description:
In this episode of MAKE IT PLAIN, we react to Jeymes Samuelâ€™s "The Book of Clarence." His message through the film is, "There is a god in yourself." We unpack the meaning of 'ye are gods' in John 10:34 and Psalm 82:6.

POLL QUESTIONS BELOW: 
Q1. Do you agree that humans are 
inherently divine?  
Yes 
No

Q2. What does the phrase "Ye are gods" mean 
that is written in Psalm 82:6 and John 10:34?
A. Each person is divine
B. Adam was made divine in God's image
C. "godsâ€ means you belong to God 
D. It means God's judges and prophets

Q3. Who was one of the judges of 
Israel in the Old Testament?
A. Othniel 
B. Abner
C. Joab
D. Lamech
